# Compose-time configuration. Contains NO secrets — only profile selection.
# Runtime secrets (DB password, JWT signing key, etc.) are injected by
# Coolify in staging/production and by developers locally if they wish to
# override the in-file defaults.
#
# Why this file is committed:
#   The default `docker compose up` must bring up the full stack so that
#   Coolify (which runs `docker compose up`) keeps deploying backend +
#   frontend without any UI configuration. Setting COMPOSE_PROFILES here
#   activates the `app` profile by default. Local devs who only want the
#   infra (postgres) can either:
#     - run `docker compose up -d postgres` (explicit, ignores profiles)
#     - or override: `COMPOSE_PROFILES= docker compose up -d`
COMPOSE_PROFILES=app
